 Yam balls by Ene for Eneskitchene. Photo Eneskitchene Yam is one of nature’s gifts that has variety: Fried yam, boiled yam, pounded yam. While all these are more familiar in Nigeria, we’d be looking at yam balls. Wondering what that is? I have got you. INGREDIENTS
Yam (Diced)
All-purpose flour
Onion (Chopped)
Cooking oil
Butter
Sardine
Egg (Separate egg white from yolk)
Bread crumbs
Red pepper (Chopped)
Green pepper (Chopped)
½ tbsp Salt
½ tbsp Thyme
Seasoning cubes METHOD Banana Stew by Jasmine Hemsley. Photo Nick Hopper NDII NA NYAMA- TANZANIAN BANANA STEW Africa is blessed with different cultures, styles, languages, and food. The amazing part is, you do not have to go too far to get the ingredients to enjoy the delicacies of another African country. Banana stew is one recipe that is delicious and will leave you wanting more. INGREDIENTS
Green banana
Beef
1 medium Onion (Diced)
3 Tomatoes (Chopped)
2 tbsp Curry powder
½ tbsp Black pepper (Ground)
1 ½ Cooking oil
1 ½ tbsp Coconut milk
¼ Cayenne pepper
1 bay leaf
2 cloves Garlic
Seasoning powder
Salt METHOD Enjoy.